headlines.description: — Patty Mills made a 3 to force overtime, Kevin Durant had 34 points, 13 rebounds and 11 assists, and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Toronto Raptors 131-129 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Short-handed Nets force overtime, beat Raptors 131-129

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry would have loved to set the record for career 3-pointers in front of his Bay Area fans.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry gets NBA record for 3-pointers, Warriors beat Knicks

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had 28 points and 13 rebounds in his return from a non-COVID-19 illness, and the Phoenix Suns held off the Portland Trail Blazers 111-107 in overtime Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayton returns to pace Suns in 111-107 win over Blazers in OT
